'''Tindivanam''' is a town and a [[municipality]] in [[Viluppuram district]] in the [[India]]n [[States and territories of India|state]] of [[Tamil Nadu]].  Important roads from north to south Tamil Nadu are passing through Tindivanam and similarly from west to east.  It was first called as 'Tindirivanam' where Tindiri is Tamarind in pure Tamil and Vanam is Jungle.  So it is called as 'Jungle Of Tamarind' in the olden days.  This name is changed as days gone past.  
Ing '''Tindivanam''' metung yang balen ampong metung a [[w:Municipality|municipality]] king [[Estadu ampong teritoriu ning India|estadu]] ning [[Tamil Nadu]], [[India]]. Daralan la keti deng mangaulagang dalan manibat king [[pangulu]] papuntang mauli, ampong manibat [[albugan]] paras king [[aslagan]]. Ibat ya kareng katayang Tamil a ''tindiri'', a mangabaldugang "sampaluk," ampong ''vanam'', a mangabaldugang "kakeuan," "gubat" o "pulû".
  
